{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QnBtX9FQoi5GMHdJiUBNiP","type":"tool_result","content":"3500\t  - `peek/src/server/exports/exporters/kol.ts` — KOL performance\n3501\t    exporter. Same bounded-ranked-list discipline as referrers\n3502\t    (`requireAtLeastOneFilter = false`, empty filter slug). Caps at\n3503\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_KOL_MAX_LIMIT`.\n3504\t\n3505\t  - `peek/src/server/exports/runner.ts` — `runPeekExport(input)`\n3506\t    orchestrator. Lifecycle:\n3507\t    1. Look up exporter; `unknown_entity` if missing.\n3508\t    2. `no_filters` if exporter requires one and none was supplied\n3509\t       (covers FR-12 \"available only for filtered tables\").\n3510\t    3. `audit_unavailable` when `NODE_ENV === \"production\"` and\n3511\t       `DATABASE_URL` is unset (covers FR-12 last bullet — exports\n3512\t       disabled in prod when audit logging is not configured).\n3513\t    4. Compute `effectiveCap = min(requested, exporter.maxRowsPerExport,\n3514\t       PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT)`; default when no cap given.\n3515\t    5. Run `exporter.fetch({sql, rowCap, filters})` to produce\n3516\t       `{rows, rowCapApplied}` (each exporter requests `rowCap+1` so the\n3517\t       cap-applied flag is honest, then trims to `rowCap`).\n3518\t    6. **Emit `peek.export` audit event BEFORE returning data**\n3519\t       (`actionId = \"export.{entity}\"`, `resourceType` from the\n3520\t       exporter, `filterSummary = \"k=v, k=v\"`, `resultCount =\n3521\t       rows.length`, `requestId` from actor). If audit insert fails\n3522\t       (writer returns `{ok:false, ...}`), runner refuses to return the\n3523\t       rows and surfaces `audit_emit_failed` so the caller never serves\n3524\t       data we could not record. FR-11 secret redaction is handled by\n3525\t       the existing audit writer (`redactPayload`) — the runner never\n3526\t       hand-rolls payload sanitation.\n3527\t    7. Build filename via `buildPeekExportFilename` and return\n3528\t       `PeekExportResult`.\n3529\t    Dependency-injectable: callers can pass `sql`, custom `registry`,\n3530\t    custom `auditWriter`, custom `env`, custom `now` for tests.\n3531\t\n3532\t  - `peek/src/server/exports/index.ts` — public re-exports:\n3533\t    `serializePeekCsv`, `buildPeekExportFilename`, `slugForFilename`,\n3534\t    registry helpers, and `runPeekExport` + types.\n3535\t\n3536\t- **Files modified** (0). No public types or backend OpenAPI changed\n3537\t  (System Invariant #9). All shapes consumed (`PeekExportEntity`,\n3538\t  `PeekExportRow`, `PeekExportFilenameInput`, `PeekExportResult`,\n3539\t  `PeekTableColumn`) were already declared in `lib/types/peek.ts`\n3540\t  during iteration 7's audit/export contract pass.\n3541\t\n3542\t- **Spec coverage** (against FR-12 acceptance criteria):\n3543\t  - **\"Exports are available only for filtered tables, not for\n3544\t    unfiltered full-table dumps.\"** — `requireAtLeastOneFilter` per\n3545\t    exporter; `claims` requires one, `referrers`/`kol` are bounded\n3546\t    ranked lists.\n3547\t  - **\"Each export has a server-side row cap.\"** — runner enforces\n3548\t    `min(requested, exporter.maxRowsPerExport,\n3549\t    PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT)`. Each exporter requests `rowCap+1` so\n3550\t    `rowCapApplied` is truthful when the source returns more.\n3551\t  - **\"Each export logs a `peek.export` operator event before returning\n3552\t    data.\"** — runner emits via `writePeekAuditEvent` BEFORE building\n3553\t    the success result. Audit emit failure → `audit_emit_failed` →\n3554\t    rows never returned.\n3555\t  - **\"Export rows use the same view model fields shown in the table\n3556\t    unless explicitly documented.\"** — each exporter's `columns` array\n3557\t    mirrors the table column ids; `fetch` calls the same query module\n3558\t    the page uses (`listReferralClaims`, `listTopReferrers`,\n3559\t    `listKolPerformance`).\n3560\t  - **\"Export filenames include entity, date, and filter slug.\"** —\n3561\t    `buildPeekExportFilename` always emits `peek-{entity}-{date}` and\n3562\t    appends `-{filterSlug}` when present.\n3563\t  - **\"Export routes require the same page-level access as the source\n3564\t    page.\"** — deferred to the next ([frontend]) iteration which will\n3565\t    place the export route under the matching `/growth/...` prefix\n3566\t    (FR-2 route policy already gates `/audit`; growth pages default to\n3567\t    business+admin per `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES`).\n3568\t  - **\"Exports are disabled in production if audit logging is not\n3569\t    configured.\"** — `isPeekAuditConfigured(env)` checks\n3570\t    `DATABASE_URL`. In production with no `DATABASE_URL`, runner\n3571\t    returns `audit_unavailable` before any SQL or audit call.\n3572\t\n3573\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n3574\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n3575\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅ (no output)\n3576\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (73 files, 820/820 — no\n3577\t    regressions; export-specific tests land in the matching\n3578\t    `[test] Export tests for required filters, row caps, filenames,\n3579\t    role checks, audit events, and prod-disabled-without-audit-config\n3580\t    behavior` iteration).\n3581\t\n3582\t- **Next**: `[frontend] Wire export actions into approved\n3583\t  growth/admin tables with disabled states + tooltip when audit\n3584\t  logging is unavailable; export routes inherit page-level access.`\n3585\t## Iteration 106 — 2026-04-26T07:40:00Z — OK\n3586\t- **Log**: iteration-106.log\n3587\t## Iteration 106 — 2026-04-26T07:41:46Z — OK\n3588\t- **Log**: iteration-106.log\n3589\t\n3590\t\n3591\t## Iteration 107 — 2026-04-26\n3592\t\n3593\t- **Item**: `[frontend] Wire export actions into approved growth/admin\n3594\t  tables with disabled states + tooltip when audit logging is\n3595\t  unavailable; export routes inherit page-level access.`\n3596\t\n3597\t- **Files added** (4):\n3598\t  - `peek/app/exports/[entity]/route.ts` — Next.js Route Handler that\n3599\t    resolves the verified actor, looks up the per-entity source page\n3600\t    via `PEEK_EXPORT_SOURCE_ROUTES`, refuses when the role cannot\n3601\t    reach that source page (FR-12 \"Export routes require the same\n3602\t    page-level access as the source page.\"), forwards URL search\n3603\t    params verbatim as exporter filters, delegates to\n3604\t    `runPeekExport`, and streams CSV with deterministic\n3605\t    `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\"...\"` and\n3606\t    `Cache-Control: no-store`. Failure-mode → status mapping:\n3607\t    `unknown_entity → 404`, `no_filters → 400`,\n3608\t    `audit_unavailable → 503`, `audit_emit_failed → 502`. The handler\n3609\t    never bypasses the audit gate — the runner emits `peek.export`\n3610\t    BEFORE rows are returned, so an unrecorded export cannot leak.\n3611\t  - `peek/src/server/exports/source-routes.ts` — server-only entity →\n3612\t    source-route map (`PEEK_EXPORT_SOURCE_ROUTES` /\n3613\t    `getSourceRouteForExportEntity`). Currently wires `referrers`,\n3614\t    `kol`, and `claims` to their `/growth/...` source pages; entities\n3615\t    declared in `PeekExportEntity` whose pages are not yet built\n3616\t    (`users`, `rounds`, `transactions`, `queue`, `audit`) are mapped\n3617\t    to `null` so the route handler fails closed with 404.\n3618\t  - `peek/src/lib/export-href.ts` — `buildExportHref(entity, filters)`\n3619\t    browser-safe URL builder that drops null/empty filter values and\n3620\t    yields a stable query string. Page-level filter state passes\n3621\t    straight through because `PeekReferralClaimFilters` already uses\n3622\t    the exporter's expected key names (`status`, `userId`,\n3623\t    `minAmountLamports`, etc.).\n3624\t  - `peek/src/components/export-action-link.tsx` — `<ExportActionLink>`\n3625\t    primitive: enabled state renders an `<a download>` with the export\n3626\t    href; disabled state renders a `role=\"button\" aria-disabled=\"true\"`\n3627\t    span with a `title` tooltip explaining why exports are off\n3628\t    (audit-unavailable copy is the default; pages can override the\n3629\t    reason — used for \"apply at least one filter\" on the claims\n3630\t    export). Component never builds the URL itself, so the access /\n3631\t    audit gate stays on the server.\n3632\t\n3633\t- **Files modified** (3):\n3634\t  - `peek/src/server/exports/index.ts` — re-export\n3635\t    `PEEK_EXPORT_SOURCE_ROUTES` and `getSourceRouteForExportEntity`\n3636\t    so route handlers can resolve the entity → source page mapping\n3637\t    via the public surface.\n3638\t  - `peek/app/growth/referrals/page.tsx` — wired `<ExportActionLink>`\n3639\t    next to **Top referrers** (`buildExportHref(\"referrers\")`) and\n3640\t    **Referral claims** (`buildExportHref(\"claims\", filters)`), using\n3641\t    the existing page-level filter state. Computes\n3642\t    `exportsEnabled = NODE_ENV \\!== \"production\" || isPeekAuditConfigured()`\n3643\t    so the disabled tooltip mirrors the runner's production gate.\n3644\t    Claims export additionally requires at least one applied filter\n3645\t    (mirrors `CLAIMS_EXPORTER.requireAtLeastOneFilter`); when no\n3646\t    filters are present the link is disabled with the\n3647\t    \"Apply at least one claims filter\" reason instead of letting the\n3648\t    runner reject the request server-side. Top referrers / KOL stay\n3649\t    enabled with no filter requirement because they ride bounded\n3650\t    ranked-list queries (`requireAtLeastOneFilter = false`).\n3651\t  - `peek/app/growth/kol/page.tsx` — wired `<ExportActionLink>` next\n3652\t    to the KOL rates table (`buildExportHref(\"kol\")`) with the same\n3653\t    `exportsEnabled` gate. KOL export needs no filter requirement\n3654\t    because the underlying `listKolPerformance` is already bounded.\n3655\t\n3656\t- **Spec coverage** (against FR-12 acceptance criteria for this\n3657\t  iter